<p>
    <strong>From the college:</strong>
    <i>A high school graduate who has taken Advanced Placement Exams and who has passed with a score of 3, 4 or 5 may receive university credit. Credit awarded will be treated as transfer credit and will count toward graduation as applicable. Additional information about transferring AP credit may be obtained from the Admission or Registrar's Office.</i>
    <br/>
    For more information, <a href="http://www.ccu.edu/admissions/faqs/" target="_blank" title="Opens a new window">view the credit policy on this college's website</a>.
